programme.title: Panorama
programme.sub-title: Terror on the Beach: Why Did It Happen? - Panorama.
programme.desc: The programme returns to the scene of the killing of 30 British tourists by a gunman on the beach at Sousse, Tunisia, in June 2015. Reporter Jane Corbin investigates whether security concerns were ignored before the attack and if lives could have been saved on the day, and asks why there wasn't tighter security or a warning to holidaymakers to stay away from Tunisia after similar incidents. She also looks at whether the Tunisian government, British tour operators and the Foreign Office bear any responsibility for what happened.(n)
